I. Definition¶

Project Overview¶

NIKKEI225 MARKET PRICE PREDICTOR¶

Nowadays Machine learning technology applies to extensive industries. Especially it uses to core of trading in the finance industry. According to news website, Goldman Sachs replaced their 600 senior traders to 200 computer engineers and made automated trading system to use Machine learning technologies. This is a great example of it's capabilities. Statistical method was popular before but recently years Machine learning method are getting more prevalence.

Recently reports shows superiority to predict using Machine Learning.
"Machine Learning with Financial Time Series Data on Google Cloud Platform"
"A deep learning framework to financial time series using stacked autoencoders and long-short term memory"

I know stock market isn't closed world and always affected from various reasons(world political situation and so on). To predict future stock price is difficult challenge even big company like GS but I'm so interested in this field trend and feel motivate. So I will tackle to use these techniques and make my own way to get better prediction. I hope it would become my good investment solution to get daily beers:-)

Problem Statement¶

The purpose of this capstone project is to build great machine learning model that can predict future stock price using historical data input. There are two type of problems. To predict future stock price is regression problem and to predict future stock price is higher or lower than today is classification problem. This project I will focus to solve regression problem to predict future stock price.

- Correction -¶

I did mistyping about previous proporsal.

WRONG: This project I will focus to solve classification problem to predict future stock price.
NEW: This project I will focus to solve regression problem to predict future stock price.

Metrics¶

Root mean squared error is good evaluation metrics to regression problem. RMSE can easy to measure what is the average deviation of the prediction from the true price and it can be compared with the mean of the true value to see whether the deviation is large or small.

Algorithms and Techniques¶

I chose to use Long Short Term Memory recurrent neural networks to this regression problem. Because input data is time sequencial data. So LSTM RNNs can be fit to solve regression problem. This trained model will be able to predict future price from specific time range input until today. (for example (n) days input returns next day predicted price.)

Benchmark¶

I chose Linear Regression as benchmark model to compare performance with LSTM. Linear Regression is still effective model for various problems. So I think easy to measure the difference of each performance.

III. Methodology¶

My simple strategy for profit¶

Assuming trained model can predict next day close price correctly.

IF predicted price is Higher than "close" price => BUY stock and SELL end of the day.
ElIF predict price is Lower than "close" price => SELL stock and BUY end of the day.

Add extra features¶

Result: Next day close price. (true price for prediction)
Variation_rate: How increase or decrease price during the day.

from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split

def generate_LR_dataset(ohlc, columns_input, train_size):

    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(ohlc[columns_input], 
                                                        ohlc["Result"], 
                                                        random_state= 0,
                                                        stratify= None,
                                                        shuffle= False,
                                                        test_size= (1 - train_size))
    return X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test

7. Strategy simulation¶

In [72]:
good_predict = 0

for index in range(len(X_test)):
    val = X_test["Result"][index] - X_test["Close"][index]
    val_pred = X_test["Predict"][index] - X_test["Close"][index]
    
    if val > 0 and val_pred > 0 or val < 0 and val_pred < 0:
        good_predict += 1

print ("Total Trade: {} Good: {} Bad: {}".format(len(X_test), good_predict, (len(X_test)-good_predict)))
print ("Predict Accuracy: {}%".format(good_predict/len(X_test)*100))

2. make dataset: (n) days historical price list and next day price¶

In [75]:
import numpy as np

def generate_lstm_dataset(ohlc, period_day, overlap= False):

    stock_price = []
    result_price = []

    # avoid overlap
    if overlap == False:
        for index in range(0, len(ohlc)-period_day, period_day):
            stock_price.append(ohlc["Close"][index : index+period_day].values)
            result_price.append(ohlc["Close"][index+period_day])
    else:
        for index in range(len(ohlc)-period_day):
            stock_price.append(ohlc["Close"][index : index+period_day].values)
            result_price.append(ohlc["Close"][index+period_day])

    stock_price = np.array(stock_price)
    
    return {"stock_price": stock_price, "result_price": result_price}

4. Build LSTM model¶

In [79]:
from keras.models import Sequential  
from keras.layers.core import Dense, Activation, Dropout
from keras.layers.recurrent import LSTM

in_out_neurons = 1
hidden_neurons = 200
length_of_sequences = period_day

LSTM_model = Sequential()

LSTM_model.add(LSTM(hidden_neurons, batch_input_shape= (None, length_of_sequences, in_out_neurons), return_sequences= False))
LSTM_model.add(Dropout(0.2))
LSTM_model.add(Dense(in_out_neurons))
LSTM_model.add(Activation("linear"))

Using TensorFlow backend.

4. Build LSTM model¶

In [108]:
import os
import time
import warnings
import numpy as np
from numpy import newaxis
from keras.layers.core import Dense, Activation, Dropout
from keras.layers.recurrent import LSTM
from keras.models import Sequential
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")

LSTM_model_v2 = Sequential()
LSTM_model_v2.add(LSTM(input_shape= (period_day, 1),
               output_dim= 100,
               return_sequences= True))

LSTM_model_v2.add(Dropout(0.2))
LSTM_model_v2.add(LSTM(100, return_sequences= False))
LSTM_model_v2.add(Dropout(0.2))
LSTM_model_v2.add(Dense(output_dim= 1))
LSTM_model_v2.add(Activation("linear"))
LSTM_model_v2.compile(loss="mse", optimizer= "rmsprop")
In [109]:
history = LSTM_model_v2.fit(X_train, y_train, batch_size= 512, nb_epoch= 50, validation_split= 0.05)

6. Predict¶

In [111]:
predict_day = 10
In [112]:
y_pred = []

for index in range(int(len(X_test) / predict_day)):
    current_frame = X_test[index * predict_day]
    predicted = []
    for day in range(predict_day):
        predicted.append(LSTM_model_v2.predict(current_frame[newaxis,:,:])[0,0])
        current_frame = current_frame[1:]
        current_frame = np.insert(current_frame, [period_day-1], predicted[-1], axis= 0)
    y_pred.append(predicted)

Refinement¶

Features and parameters¶

  • Adding features
    "Variation_rate" which represent how increase or decrease price during the day.

  • Normalize parameter
    Normalization is many ways to do and I did divided by mean value this time. Relative value is more effective for making better model not only absolute value like close price.

Hyper parameter¶

  • LSTM
    Still need deep understanding about each parameter but I was trying to find nice balance between calcutation time and prediction result.
    Continous output seem kinds of possibility but need more time to tune up.

V. Conclusion¶

Reflection¶

This capstone project, I made "NIKKEI 225 PREDICTOR" which are Linear Regression model and LSTM model using historical price data. As my previous capstone proposal consideration, LSTM model did better prediction and I can understand how advantage that LSTM can input continuous time sequencial data but at the same time to I felt what difficlut and endless challenge to predict stock price and machine learning.

Found Interesting¶

Prediction result changed dramalically depends on feature selection and algorithm. It's so fun and I cloud feel possibility about LSTM algorithm. I'm still checking and tuning about my LSTM model.

Found difficult¶

It was so hard to find proper way to use and selection of each algorithms and parameters also how to avoid overfit. Method should change depends on dataset every time and it was like a endless try and error. I felt that I need more deep understanding and experience about LSTM and even Linear Regression.

Next improvement and challenge¶

I chose LSTM as a core algorithm in this project.
But I know there are a lot of different algorithms to solve.

I'm interested in and will try.

  • Convolutional Nural Network
    https://lucenaresearch.com/timeseries-convolutional/
  • Deep Reinforcement Learning
    https://medium.com/@gaurav1086/machine-learning-for-algorithmic-trading-f79201c8bac6

I am also interested in the difference of performance compared to the classification problem.
It's good challenge to combine with sentiment analysis result from SNS like twitter and news website to get even better prediction as well.

It seems endless challenges but I have endless motivation. So I will continue to learning:-)
